<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="772" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conference 184.01502/19:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-02"><hi rend="italic">May 2,
                                1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received in Paris May 3, 9:15
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>350. Following from <persName corresp="#p_GLCW1">Greene</persName>:</p>
                        <p>“29, May 2nd. Legation’s 346, April 29th.<note n="11" xml:id="d772fn11">Not printed.</note> Northern Esthonian front still firm despite
                            serious bombardment Narva, entailing destruction 150 houses, and 5,000
                            homeless. Southern front weak at several points, but temporarily
                            strengthened and firm. Need of food supplies in outlying districts
                            urgent. Important that food ships sail at once for Reval”.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>